author: J-W Staff Reports
title: Jones, Prescott lead Lions’ runners
text:
October 11, 2015 
Advertisement 
Shawnee  Lawrence High’s Morgan Jones placed second, and the LHS girls placed fifth among six teams in the Carl Owczarzak Fall Classic Saturday at Shawnee Mission Park. 
Garrett Prescott led the Lions’ boys with a 10th-place finish, and LHS took fourth out of eight teams. Anna DeWitt was next for the LHS girls with an 11th-place finish, and Carson Jumping Eagle took 15th place for the Lawrence High boys.
